text: Robert James Ellicott (15 April 1927 - 31 October 2022) was an Australian lawyer, politician and judge. He was born in Moree, New South Wales. Ellicott was one of only six politicians to have been in both the Parliament of Australia and the Federal Court of Australia. He was elected as the Liberal member for the Division of Wentworth in the 1974 election. He was Attorney- General in the Fraser Ministry from 1975 to 1977. Ellicott died on 31 October 2022, at the age of 95. ==References== Category:1927 births Category:2022 deaths Category:Australian lawyers Category:Australian judges Category:Politicians from New South Wales
